{
  "text": "In which C in is the inlet concentration and C out is the outlet concentration of compound, which is corrected for volume change in the segment using phenol red concentration in the inlet and outlet tubing. Q is the flow rate (0.2 mL/min), r is the rat intestinal radius (0.18 cm), and l is the length of the segment [CITATION_1] .",
